Supplemental legal references (Idaho)

- Idaho Code § 9-714 (Title 9, Chapter 7 — media source confidentiality) protects unpublished notes and source identities created during newsgathering.
- Idaho Code § 28-5301 et seq. (Title 28, Chapter 53 — Idaho Digital Assets Act) classifies digital assets as intangible personal property and provides control/perfection rules for virtual currency and other digital records.
- Uniform Commercial Code Article 12 (controllable electronic records) supplies control/transfer standards in jurisdictions that have adopted the 2022 UCC amendments; Idaho has not adopted Article 12 as of April 2026, but equivalent rights are reserved where applicable.

These citations provide statutory context and do not modify the license terms above.
